      23: { rank: 9, highlight: 'Fear Factory\'s mechanical, industrial-doom crush', reason: 'Raymond Herrera\'s programmed-precision drumming with Fear Factory built industrial metal\'s mechanical, tempo-locked heaviness — slow, grinding passages on "Demanufacture" and "Obsolete" that trade doom metal\'s organic swing for machine-like repetition, arriving at the same crushing, tonnage-first destination through an industrial lens' },
      14: { rank: 10, highlight: 'Tool\'s slow-building, atmospheric weight', reason: 'Danny Carey\'s work with Tool since 1990 builds long, slowly evolving compositions where deceleration itself becomes the emotional and atmospheric device doom metal has always depended on, using extreme patience to intensify weight rather than momentum' },
