      61: { rank: 8, highlight: 'Trivium\'s modern groove-thrash synthesis', reason: 'Alex Bent\'s work with Trivium blends technical death metal precision with groove metal\'s syncopated riff-locking, representing how the genre\'s 1990s vocabulary continues shaping 21st-century metal drummers raised on Pantera and Lamb of God in equal measure' },
      2: { rank: 9, highlight: 'Slipknot\'s groove-metal-informed chaos', reason: 'Joey Jordison\'s drumming with Slipknot channeled Pantera\'s syncopated groove through nu-metal\'s percussive chaos, his precise, aggressive pocket playing on "Iowa" (2001) demonstrating groove metal\'s direct influence on the nu-metal generation that broke through alongside it' },
