      3: { rank: 2, highlight: '"The Atomic Clock" — Pearl Reference Pure across four decades', reason: 'Gene Hoglan has been a Pearl Drums endorser for many years, running a Pearl Reference Pure kit with a Pearl Reference 14"x6.5" brass snare and Pearl Demon Drive double pedal, having started on a Pearl Session Elite kit for Death\'s 1993 "Individual Thought Patterns." That Pearl relationship has carried across Testament, Dark Angel, and Dethklok, spanning more bands and subgenres than almost any other drummer\'s brand history in MetalForge\'s database. Hoglan earns rank #2 for the broadest cross-band Pearl documentation on this list.' },
      8: { rank: 3, highlight: 'Pearl Reference Pure — Korn\'s versatile groove engine', reason: 'Ray Luzier is a Pearl Drums and Sabian Cymbals endorser, running a Pearl Reference Pure kit in custom finishes with a Pearl Reference 14"x5" brass or steel snare, versatile enough to handle Korn\'s complex, downtuned grooves and heavy moments with equal precision. Luzier earns rank #3 for bringing a fully documented Pearl setup into one of nu-metal\'s most influential and longest-running bands.' },
      52: { rank: 4, highlight: 'Pearl Masterworks Maple — Dream Theater\'s technical virtuoso', reason: 'Mike Mangini runs a massive Pearl Masterworks Maple kit in custom configuration, with multiple Pearl Reference snares (14"x5" and 14"x6.5"), a Pearl Eliminator Redline double pedal, a Pearl Roadster throne, and Roland TD-50 triggers for the polyrhythmic complexity that defines his tenure as Dream Theater\'s drummer since 2010. Mangini earns rank #4 for one of the most electronically integrated Pearl setups documented in MetalForge\'s gear data.' },
