      14: { rank: 3, highlight: 'Remo Emperor & Powerstroke 3 — Tool\'s dynamic range', reason: 'Danny Carey runs Remo Emperor Coated heads on toms and snare with a Remo Powerstroke 3 on his bass drum, a combination chosen for the dynamic headroom Tool\'s material demands — quiet enough for the band\'s ambient passages, durable enough for its explosive polyrhythmic peaks. The two-ply Emperor\'s controlled overtone and the Powerstroke 3\'s built-in muffling ring give Carey a single head configuration that doesn\'t need retuning between Tool\'s quietest and loudest sections. Carey earns rank #3 for a Remo setup built specifically around dynamic range rather than raw durability.' },
      17: { rank: 4, highlight: 'Evans G2 Coated — Lamb of God\'s dry, direct punch', reason: 'Chris Adler runs Evans G2 Coated batter heads across Lamb of God\'s Mapex Black Panther kit, a two-ply design that delivers the dry, focused punch his syncopated, riff-locking grooves need without the extra overtone control a triple-ply head would add. That straightforward G2 choice matches the no-frills precision of his Mapex Chris Adler Signature snare and Promark TX5AXW signature sticks. Adler earns rank #4 for a documented Evans model that mirrors groove metal\'s preference for direct, uncomplicated attack.' },
      13: { rank: 5, highlight: 'Evans EC2 Frosted & G2 Clear — Dream Theater\'s dense arrangements', reason: 'Mike Portnoy runs Evans EC2 Frosted batter heads on toms and an Evans G2 Clear on his bass drum, a combination built for Dream Theater\'s dense progressive arrangements — the EC2\'s built-in overtone control keeps rapid tom fills from smearing together, while the G2 Clear\'s brighter attack cuts through the layered instrumentation of his most technical passages. Portnoy earns rank #5 for a two-model Evans setup documented across sixteen years on DW and his return to Tama alike.' },
      12: { rank: 6, highlight: 'Evans Genera G1 — thrash\'s clarity at speed', reason: 'Charlie Benante runs Evans Genera G1 batter heads across his Tama Starclassic Maple kit, a single-ply design that keeps Anthrax\'s thrash patterns bright and articulate rather than dampened, matching the cutting attack of his Vic Firth signature sticks. The G1\'s minimal muffling suits Benante\'s precise, high-speed skank-beat technique, where head-generated overtone control would blur the separation between rapid single strokes. Benante earns rank #6 for a documented Evans model built around thrash\'s demand for clarity at speed.' },
      20: { rank: 7, highlight: 'Remo Powerstroke 3 Clear — black metal\'s blast-beat durability', reason: 'Hellhammer runs Remo Powerstroke 3 Clear batter heads across his Pearl Reference/Masters kit, a built-in-muffled design that gives Mayhem\'s blast-beat-driven black metal a controlled, focused low end instead of an uncontrolled ring. The Powerstroke 3\'s dot-and-ring muffling system does mechanically what a separate damping pad would otherwise need to do, simplifying his live setup across decades of Mayhem\'s turbulent touring history. Hellhammer earns rank #7 for a Remo model chosen specifically for black metal\'s blast-beat durability demands.' },
      21: { rank: 8, highlight: 'Evans Hydraulic Black — built to survive the gravity blast', reason: 'Pete Sandoval runs Evans Hydraulic Black batter heads across his Pearl Export/Masters kit, a double-ply, oil-filled design built for maximum durability and a fast, dry decay under the extreme, sustained blast-beat abuse that made him death metal\'s gravity-blast pioneer. That oil-filled construction resists the head fatigue lighter, single-ply heads suffer under Morbid Angel\'s punishing live schedule. Sandoval earns rank #8 for an Evans model chosen purely for survival under extreme metal\'s most demanding technique.' },
      28: { rank: 9, highlight: 'Evans G2 Clear — reliability at 270 BPM', reason: 'Flo Mounier runs Evans G2 Clear batter heads across his Pearl Demon Drive-equipped kit, a two-ply design durable enough to hold up to his documented 270 BPM tempos without needing retuning mid-set, among the fastest sustained tempos in MetalForge\'s entire drummer database. The G2\'s straightforward two-ply construction gives Mounier consistent rebound and attack at a speed where head failure would end a performance outright. Mounier earns rank #9 for an Evans model selected purely for reliability at technical death metal\'s extreme-speed tier.' },
